We found this gem walking around and have been returning as often as we can.  The staff is knowledgable and made my family feel very comfortable. Food is excellent, drink selection is awesome, and their specials are great too. Cant wait til our next visit! Great job to all the staff!
The chicken tenders were huge. More likely breast. The portion of fries was a bit stingy in my experience. However service was prompt.

Very nice place. Food and drinks were good.

It was a little disappointment on a Friday night.. Me and my friends went for a couple of drinks and food....the ambience was great.... I guess they were low staffed and it took almost 5mins for someone to make us seated.. Though they had good selection of whiskeys and other drinks.. The  kitchen was closed by 8.30 pm which was totally unexpected and we couldn't order any food... Not sure of his name.. But there was only one guy serving all and he made sure we got everything timely.. Thanks to him..

Gets pretty crowded from all the office workers, they have specials from time to time. They have really good boneless wings served in some kind of wooded plaque. I’ve also had their burger and it was legit good.
Dependable lunch spot. Short hours are kept, but the location is key.
Solid choice in a sea of high priced food downtown. And they have tater tots. Cant go wrong with tots!
Exelent
Food is great but watch out for long lines at lunchtime.

Decent low key place for drinks and snacks after work if you work in the loop. One of the few "casual" bars along Wacker. They recently remodeled and the place definitely looks better. Staff is friendly and service is good. You'll see a lot of the business / loop office crowd in here 4-7... Past that it's happy hour spill over. I would imagine this place is dead late night and weekends (could be wrong though, I go to bed at 9 pm lol!)
Drinks were good, service was a little slow

I came in for lunch yesterday and we normally eat here after. Yesterday the service was terrible. Laura was our server (she had red hair) never even came to a full stop when coming by our table, there wasn't a huge crowd and she was very rushed with her service. She would continue walking when we were talking to her. Won't be coming back any time soon.
Good food, not too expensive at all!

Nice lunch spot on LaSalle.  Hey have happy hour specials but I usually just go there for lunch. So no comment on the drinks.  Should probably get reservations no matter what time you go.  They have the usual half sandwich and soup special.  The real star are the tator tots. Those are crunchy and delicious! If you do go during happy hour the giant pretzel is amazing.
Good food to order for delivery.
Nice atmosphere. Went during lunch the burger I had was delicious!
Great place for a private party! Food spread and drink package was excellent

Enjoyed the happy hour. Wish there were more cocktail options on the happy hour list but the mules were good and the food as well. The music and jokes flashing across the screen were a nice addition as well.
Tasty appetizers and decent martinis. Cozy booths for conversation. Good option for after work in the loop.
Great food, great people.
I go there for trivia and the chicken fingers are the best I've ever had. The wait staff is attentive and really nice.
Long wait but food and drinks were decent.
Top lunch spot
Staff are really friendly, their tatter tots are fantastic, the sandwiches are OK hence 4 stars.

Nice quaint venue in a great location on North LaSalle. Food was really good especially the tortilla soup and grilled cheese. Service was a little slow as it seemed that they were understaffed. Otherwise real good experience.

Awesome food, especially the burger and fries! The atmosphere is cool and laid back although service has been slow. They just changed their menu for dinner and got rid of some of our favorites, so we probably won't be going back sadly.  **EDIT: we did end up going back with friends, and the new menu was still delicious! Service was slow, but the food did not disappoint! We had a burger, steak sliders, wings, and fries - all delicious  ***EDIT: tonight we had hair in our food and the order was wrong. Definitely will not return and would advise others to stay away.
Fantastic servers and food
I love  this place

Nice downtown place. Food was pretty decent, especially the sliders. Chicken were our favorite but the steak ones were good too. Trivia night was interesting but we had fun and won prizes. Plenty of TVs to watch whatever you want. We really liked it.

Usually good for lunch but when it's really busy the quality of the food goes down. Got a turkey burger which is usually juicy but ended up dry and a little burnt. But I waited so long for food that I just had to eat and go.

This is my go to stop after work with my colleagues. The staff is always very accommodating with special requests & the food is outstanding. There are plenty of televisions to watch any game on. The fish tacos are my favorite with the spicy arbol sauce, but don't miss out on the oysters either!
Good happy hour specials.
Clean, friendly and great food and drinks.
Good food and a great atmosphere. Perfect for lunch or after work drinks - although the service during the lunch hour could be faster
Go for Happy Hour! Great drink & app specials!

Went here for a work party; we had the back area and a dedicated bartender. Food served (small buffet) was definitely better than expected. 5-7 draft beers on tap, a good variety. Definitely exceeded expectations; we'll come back here for another work thing in the future.
Decent food

Good loop bar with above average bar food. On Monday nights, the trivia game is fun.  The hour vary at night.  Technically it is open to 11 pm but if there are no customers,  they close at 9 pm.
Nice place, good bartenders. Perfect for a low key happy hour.
Because Luis i the best!

The food is really good and service is fair enough. Their fries are fantastic but they have good fish tacos. There are other healthy options too when you're not in a carnivore state.  Prices are on par with everything else in the loop but the food is what brings me back. Well that, and it's literally 1/2 block from the office...
Came in for a drink and a quick bite. Drinks were good but the food left a lot to be desired.
Good ambiance. Great location.
Great industry discount!
Soup and sandwich with tater tots over lunch. Very good!

Went to Sibebar for a rehearsal dinner.  Great atmosphere for a cocktail/buffet style dinner. There was adequate space for mingling and enough tables for seating when eating. The wait staff was very attentive and all had great attitudes (it was an open bar).  Great service overall. Shredded beef taco bar was delicious; did not skimp on the fixings! Also had wonderful soft pretzel balls with cheese sauce as a passed hors d'oeuvre.
Great lunch spot for business meetings in the heart of downtown Chicago, IL.
The staff is friendly and the food is tasty.
Great service and food.
I love slidebar.  This place is conveniently located in the loop, at lasalle and wacker. Great beer and drinks, and the food is pretty solid as well.

Hosted a work event here. Great customer service planning the event. During the event, the staff was super friendly and attentive. They went above and beyond. Plus, the food is great! Delicious guacamole and cookie skillets! Really nice music they play too. Be sure to check them out. Warning though they do get super packed especially around happy hour time.
Consistently good.
Good food
In the handful of times I've been here, I've received timely service and good food/drinks. They have a great concise selection of apps and food all for a great price.

Two Corona beers...$13.50.  Never agsin.
Good service and food! Ask for the specials!
Sidebar is our go to when we're downtown to go to an event as it's never super packed! This is a great happy hour bar! Good food, some creative delicious cocktails and good beer.
Service was good, lettuce wraps and cheeseburger were good. Prices are not bad for the loop...

If you are vegan, this is a nice try. Their humus with guacamole is good, what you would expect it to be. Then, for sides they have a great spinach couscous salad. Service was super  - as you would expect for raw foods. Price is fair for the area.
Wonderful staff and great food. I was in town visiting and the staff offered numerous local places and things to enjoy while in town.

Came on a Thursday around 7:45 and was told the kitchen was closing at 8. An hour later they basically kicked us out because they decided to close early since it was pretty empty. They also only had bottled beers because their drafts weren't working for some reason.
Decent for a quick beer, a little on the pricy side.
United airlines had a post race party here after the chase corporate challenge. It was a great space, food was typical bar food but the service was great.

Nice spot, a little pricey but good drinks and nice atmosphere.

Pricey!

Great food! Service was okay. Very nice, but accuracy on our orders was way off throughout the night.
Better than average loop bar/grille for work happy hour. Food is better than average since they are a Four Corners bar.
Good drinks, and food... super convenient for me since I work in the same building.
Standard after work bar.  Good beer selection.  Some of the appetizers we got were actually pretty bad.  Otherwise, relaxed atmosphere and well priced.
great service and AMAZING fries! deserves a 5 just for the cajun seasoning!
Great place for lunch.

Great spot for lunch, there isn't another bar and grill type of joint within 2 or 3 blocks so this place has stuck around.
Went to a cool preview event here. Good food and drink, just gets crowded fast!
Great spot for a work lunch. Staff is friendly and responsive, and the food is good.
We had our work holiday party here and we enjoyed it.  The beer selection and service were great.
Pricey for decent food and slow service. Literally waited an hour for a burger and a grilled cheese. I am unlikely to return here.

Right by the Clark and Lake Blue Line this is one awesome bar that is very very convenient for me. I really like the food and there mule drink which was really yummy. The lettuce cups, tacos, and there sub sandwich aj jour was delicious as well. Oh those lettuce cups with the peanut sauce almost forgot to add the sauce was great! 5 stars from the Richlatino Chicagorican Fedora Hat wearer that speaks Spanglish not Spanish that can guarantee making this one of the stops when traveling in Chi-Town Downtown.
Sidebar Grille is a great happy hour bar. The offer an extensive drink menu and quite a few food options. While I've not eaten there, they do offer gluten free options.

I love four corners bars because you always know what you are going to get when you walk in the door. Great beer, great wine, and great food. The space is a little cramped, but most bars located in the loop are!  Wish they could expand!

Like most places in the area they are absolutely slammed during the lunch rush but if you get there a little early or a little late it isn't bad on finding a table. The food is good and the wait staff is friendly. With how close together the tables are it can get a little loud in here so probably not the best place for a meeting and maybe not for a date if you plan on doing a lot of talking but its good for hanging out with friends.

Sidebar is another great restaurant from Four Corners Tavern Group.  It's in kind of a strange location, as in not close to a lot of other bars.  However, the upscale bar food is always delicious - my favorites include the Southwest Salad and the Skillet Cookie.  The beer selection is good as well.

I've only been to sidebar Grille for happy hour and snacks, but the room is warm and welcoming, the people are friendly, and the beer selection is pretty good. If you're in the area you should we stop and for a drink and check the place out.

This bar and grill is good compared to what else is around in the Loop.  One thing about Sidebar, it is always busy.  Don't plan on just showing up over the noon hour and grab a table.  You will have to wait.

Rude waitress and a runny "medium" burger lead to a sub-par meal.  When they have dollar cheeseburgers, make sure you ask specifically for the special dollar cheeseburger. Otherwise you're charged 11 bucks and get a sarcastic "Really?"
